17:37.186 --> 17:44.555
Cindy, Sally, you know, I don't know.

17:44.575 --> 17:47.579
But it's a good theory, though, right?

17:49.982 --> 17:54.668
Until only Jesus was left with the woman still standing there.

17:54.909 --> 17:56.711
Now, notice she still hadn't said, I'm sorry.

17:56.911 --> 17:57.933
Oh, I'm so embarrassed.

17:57.953 --> 17:58.333
Nothing.

17:58.393 --> 17:59.274
She hadn't said anything.

18:00.656 --> 18:05.362
And Jesus straightened up and asked her, woman, where are your accusers?

18:06.146 --> 18:07.908
Has no one condemned you?"

18:07.928 --> 18:09.650
And she goes, no, because you ran them all off.

18:09.950 --> 18:10.411
No one.

18:10.971 --> 18:15.036
And then you've got to know this line because this shows the immense forgiveness and love for God.

18:15.316 --> 18:21.323
And I think somebody in one of our rooms today might need to hear this, that neither do I condemn you.

18:22.584 --> 18:26.048
In other words, I'm not going to let this be the most condemning thing that ever happened to you.

18:26.168 --> 18:27.430
This is not the end of your life.

18:28.411 --> 18:29.432
He gave her grace.

18:29.932 --> 18:31.314
He didn't leave her there by the way.

18:31.554 --> 18:33.676
Some people read that and says, oh God, I'll just let you off the hook.

18:33.696 --> 18:34.017
No, no, no.

18:34.257 --> 18:35.939
He gave her grace and then he gives her truth.

18:35.959 --> 18:37.961
Now go leave your life of sin.

18:38.021 --> 18:43.867
He led her into both because God has a wonderful destiny and restoration for our lives.

18:44.688 --> 18:47.591
And I just thought about all the lessons that we could learn from this story.

18:47.611 --> 18:51.195
There's three I wanna focus on as it relates to the forgiveness of God.

18:51.215 --> 18:55.800
And the first one is that the forgiveness of Jesus comes at our worst moments.

18:56.741 --> 18:57.582
So let me say it this way.

18:57.602 --> 19:01.106
He was offering it before she even asked for it.

19:02.178 --> 19:07.927
He was already in the middle of her worst day giving her something she hadn't even asked for yet.

19:08.007 --> 19:09.129
Are y'all seeing that everybody?

19:09.610 --> 19:17.923
And I say that to you that God's not over in a corner in so holy space waiting for you to crawl hands and feet back to him begging for his forgiveness.

19:18.263 --> 19:21.548
No, he's looking for you in the middle of your worst moments.

19:22.069 --> 19:27.858
And it's ready to step in and say, if you'll step toward me, I do not condemn you, you can leave your life of sin.

19:27.878 --> 19:28.619
He's already there.

19:29.040 --> 19:30.322
That's what I want you to see though.

19:32.642 --> 19:39.208
The second thing I love for you to see in this story is that for the forgiveness of Jesus doesn't ignore justice, it shifts it.

19:39.809 --> 19:49.037
So he actually did follow the law because he knew the stones that they were getting ready to throw would be the stones that would actually end up on Jesus' body while he hung on the cross.

19:49.398 --> 19:52.300
He was gonna take the penalty for what she did.

19:52.361 --> 19:54.823
So he doesn't actually ignore truth.

19:55.063 --> 19:58.286
He actually shifts the justice to himself.

19:58.306 --> 19:58.767
He's ready.

19:59.247 --> 19:59.948
Let me say it this way.

20:00.088 --> 20:02.450
He's ready to take the blame for everything you did.

20:04.322 --> 20:05.203
He's ready to.

20:05.223 --> 20:06.565
He shifts it to himself.

20:07.026 --> 20:08.267
And by the way, it was paid for.

20:08.367 --> 20:09.870
Somebody got stoned on.

20:10.190 --> 20:11.512
It was actually Jesus on that cross.

20:11.592 --> 20:12.653
Are you following me, everybody?

20:13.474 --> 20:20.284
And then the last thing I just thought in this story is that the forgiveness of Jesus not only removes the past, but it restores the future.

20:20.404 --> 20:22.947
He wasn't just focused on what she did.

20:22.967 --> 20:26.772
He was focused on who she could become still.

20:28.234 --> 20:28.995
Let me say it this way.

20:29.236 --> 20:30.898
You can't go too far.

20:31.266 --> 20:37.235
to not only receive the forgiveness of God, but also have your life completely turned around where God uses you again.

20:37.295 --> 20:38.957
Come on, give him praise together, everybody.

20:39.699 --> 20:40.700
It's just a beautiful thing.

20:44.045 --> 20:46.408
And I think somebody who needs to hear all of this.

20:47.670 --> 20:51.736
In fact, let me say it to you, on behalf of the one who loves you deeply, look at my eyes.

20:52.457 --> 20:53.459
He doesn't condemn you.

20:54.360 --> 20:55.923
You can go leave your life as sin.

20:56.804 --> 20:58.226
And I truly believe somebody

20:58.722 --> 20:59.423
needs to hear that.

20:59.463 --> 21:00.525
So what do we do with this?

21:00.585 --> 21:05.192
What do we do with the goodness of God expressed to us through Jesus in that kind of way?

21:05.453 --> 21:06.935
What should be our response?

21:06.955 --> 21:08.477
Let me offer three for you today.

21:08.497 --> 21:10.300
Number one, receive it.

21:12.043 --> 21:14.987
And I say this for every person who has a hard time receiving it.

21:16.209 --> 21:20.075
Like some of you have so self-condemned yourself.

21:20.696 --> 21:25.684
You think about your mistakes over and over and over again.

21:25.744 --> 21:26.866
You're in,

21:27.010 --> 21:28.333
You're not in conviction.

21:28.393 --> 21:29.616
That's what Holy Spirit does.

21:29.636 --> 21:31.120
You're in condemnation.

21:31.901 --> 21:38.136
And by the way, modern psychology has already affirmed what scripture teaches about this.

21:38.557 --> 21:41.444
And that is that guilt and shame will produce something.

21:41.464 --> 21:45.874
It produces you withdrawing from family, friends, God.

21:46.018 --> 21:47.520
It produces self-punishment.

21:47.640 --> 21:51.004
If you live a life of shame, you don't like yourself.

21:51.465 --> 21:55.109
On the other hand, when you receive the grace of God, and again, psychology's proved this.

21:55.350 --> 22:02.398
When you receive the grace and the love and the forgiveness of God, it produces gratitude, intimacy, generosity.

22:02.458 --> 22:05.142
You're a brand new person when you can receive this.

22:06.383 --> 22:13.252
And so then I thought about, God, if I was to lead our church into something that'll help them receive it, what would that be?

22:13.352 --> 22:14.994
I'm gonna offer something that almost sounds

22:15.074 --> 22:18.739
counterintuitive or it's actually the opposite of what you should do.

22:19.459 --> 22:21.142
Because I was thinking about the Lord's Prayer.

22:21.202 --> 22:22.363
I love prayer models.

22:22.403 --> 22:23.044
You guys know that.

22:23.064 --> 22:26.628
I've written prayer books and I love prayer plans and prayer models.

22:26.749 --> 22:32.456
And one of my favorite prayers to pray is not the prayer itself, but the phrases of the Lord's Prayer.

22:32.816 --> 22:35.239
And one of the phrases of the Lord's Prayer is forgive us.

22:36.701 --> 22:41.046
To which you gotta think about if he's already forgiven you of all your sins, why do we need to say that?

22:42.128 --> 22:44.050
Like why would we ask God to forgive us

22:44.898 --> 22:46.040
If he already has.

22:47.582 --> 22:53.750
And I'll say, Lord, why do you want us to daily say forgive us, forgive us for something again that he's already done?

22:53.790 --> 22:58.977
And I feel like I have an answer for you that's gonna help some of you walk in this and receive the forgiveness of God.

22:59.337 --> 23:07.689
And that is we ask God to forgive us not because he hasn't, but so we can remember that he actually has.

23:08.570 --> 23:14.738
What if every day you have a time with God and when you get to this part, forgive us our trespasses?

23:14.914 --> 23:22.041
And I want to thank you that all of my sin past, present, and future has been paid for by the precious blood of Jesus.

23:22.462 --> 23:29.749
I think it actually would draw you so close to Him and allow you to be able to receive His love and His forgiveness in your life.

23:29.829 --> 23:30.510
Amen, everybody?

23:30.550 --> 23:31.591
Are you understanding that?

23:32.091 --> 23:33.513
And I want you to try that.

23:33.533 --> 23:40.380
I want you to, when you pray, when you spend time with God, not only ask Him to do it, but thinking that He already has.

23:41.161 --> 23:42.482
Because here's what I know this.

23:43.298 --> 23:51.508
is that the more you can receive this, the more you'll fall in love with him, and the more you fall in love with him, the easier and the better he is to follow.

23:52.209 --> 23:55.493
It's so important that you have the right view of God.

23:55.713 --> 23:58.276
Your view of God determines your relationship with God.

23:58.997 --> 24:00.659
And I want you to see him as a loving father.

24:00.679 --> 24:01.661
I'll tell you this quick little story.

24:02.361 --> 24:05.726
Years ago when Tammy and I, our kids were very, very little.

24:06.707 --> 24:10.071
We had just had our fifth, and it felt like a lot.

24:10.111 --> 24:12.594
Like five kids is a lot.

24:12.738 --> 24:16.483
And when they're in that, come on parents, in that seven, eight, nine, 10 year, oh, it's just a lot.

24:16.503 --> 24:17.785
And there's always something, right?

24:18.326 --> 24:19.928
And I'm kind of conditioned to that.

24:19.968 --> 24:21.450
Tammy's way more gracious than I am.

24:21.490 --> 24:22.292
I'm a little bit more okay.

24:22.312 --> 24:23.093
What did they do today?

24:23.293 --> 24:24.114
You know that kind of thing?

24:24.154 --> 24:34.028
And I came home and we had a beautiful bed that had a tall headboard, wooden headboard and a smaller lower wooden footboard.

24:34.569 --> 24:40.978
And when I came in and I took my sport coat off and I threw it across the footboard, I was undressing from work.

24:41.410 --> 24:49.780
I noticed that one of the knobs of the foot board was now smaller than the other knob, and there was wood shavings at the bottom on the floor.

24:50.441 --> 24:54.927
That one of the kids had gotten a knife and decided to go carving on the knob.

24:55.307 --> 24:58.291
I mean, it was like significantly smaller than the other one.

25:00.353 --> 25:04.699
Bloods boiling in my head, just like, oh, my goodness.

25:05.380 --> 25:06.381
And I know who it is.

25:09.184 --> 25:10.546
Parents, come on, where y'all at?

25:11.842 --> 25:15.948
I won't tell you which one so he can protect his anonymity, but it's David.

25:16.028 --> 25:16.809
Okay, it's David.

25:18.893 --> 25:19.553
I know it's David.

25:20.615 --> 25:26.804
So I had a, I had a, like the kids knew if I whistled, like, real loud, they, like the Von Trapp family, they all came in.

25:26.884 --> 25:28.206
They lined it up.

25:28.226 --> 25:29.388
Yes, sir.

25:29.568 --> 25:29.949
Yes, sir.

25:30.510 --> 25:30.870
Yes, sir.

25:30.910 --> 25:31.371
Yes, sir.

25:31.431 --> 25:31.792
Yes, sir.

25:32.533 --> 25:36.018
And they're all, and I'm, you know, like I'm talking to all five, but I'm really only talking to one.

25:38.146 --> 25:39.968
Who's been whittling on the bed?"

25:39.988 --> 25:58.946
I said to David, and the sweetest one in our family, the most gentle, the kindest, the funniest, the nicest, never anything wrong, Jonathan, because... And immediately confesses to doing this, and he did with this little sheepish smile on his face, Daddy, I did it.

26:00.227 --> 26:07.954
And the way he did that, y'all, I was biting out my cheeks, trying not to laugh, you know, because of the way he

26:08.098 --> 26:18.228
came to me about, and the question is, why did he have the confidence not only to do it immediately, but also so honestly and transparently, you know why?

26:18.248 --> 26:18.729
Because he knew.

26:18.749 --> 26:21.812
He had a confidence in his father.

26:22.853 --> 26:25.235
And I went, well, bro, why did you do that?

26:25.536 --> 26:27.217
And now I'm smiling, I'm not mad anymore.

26:27.237 --> 26:28.539
I'm like, why did you do that to my parents?

26:32.082 --> 26:33.784
And of course parents, y'all know exactly what he said.

26:33.804 --> 26:35.666
I don't know.

26:38.114 --> 26:39.215
I said, well, don't do that again.

26:39.255 --> 26:39.676
Yes.

26:40.938 --> 26:41.799
And he went off and played.

26:43.080 --> 26:50.910
And it taught me something that day that I always wanted to have a relationship with my kids who had the ability to nearly say, Daddy, I did this.

26:51.270 --> 26:53.393
I know it was wrong, but also know you.

26:55.235 --> 26:56.317
And I know you're still going to love me.

26:56.337 --> 26:57.678
I'm not going to get kicked out of the family.

26:58.479 --> 26:58.740
Come on.

26:58.760 --> 27:00.081
Somebody needs to hear this today.

27:00.101 --> 27:04.487
You need to receive the forgiveness of our God, everybody.

27:04.507 --> 27:06.069
You need to receive them.

27:06.089 --> 27:07.090
That's the way he loves you.

27:10.370 --> 27:17.299
The second we've taught you a ton, I won't spend a lot of time on it, but we need also release this forgiveness to others.

27:17.319 --> 27:24.509
And I always say that you actually cannot do it until you've received it yourself, but once you've received it yourself, it is important for you to be a forgiver.

27:25.150 --> 27:28.254
I say this in the middle of a culture that has about lost its mind.

27:30.317 --> 27:30.517
Okay?

27:32.359 --> 27:34.422
That we gotta get the anger out of our hearts.

27:35.964 --> 27:37.506
We gotta get the hatred out of our hearts.

27:38.848 --> 27:40.210
And if you have it in your heart,

27:40.322 --> 27:45.169
If you're mad and angry about somebody, even if they deserve it, it's going to kill you long before it kills them.

27:46.391 --> 27:47.132
That's just the fact.

27:47.773 --> 27:50.216
Unforgiveness is a stopper of everything.

27:50.396 --> 27:50.737
Beautiful.

27:50.857 --> 27:51.238
Everything.

27:51.558 --> 27:52.119
Everything.

27:53.281 --> 27:56.445
Everything.

27:56.465 --> 27:57.807
And we think we're punishing them.

27:57.847 --> 27:58.728
You're not punishing them.

27:58.748 --> 27:59.630
You're punishing yourself.

28:00.711 --> 28:08.242
If you're carrying something around about a family member or somebody in culture, the opposing party of whatever your party is,

28:08.450 --> 28:14.438
We're so picking sides these days and we build all this stuff in our heart and you think you're punishing them by holding that against them.

28:15.119 --> 28:21.528
I heard someone say unforgiveness is like setting yourself on fire and hoping your enemy dies from smoke inhalation.

28:24.813 --> 28:26.335
You ain't hurting them, you hurting you.

28:26.375 --> 28:34.807
And when we forgive, it does more for us than it does for them.

28:36.349 --> 28:37.170
So what do we do?

28:37.250 --> 28:50.968
Here's the thought, follow the Bible that says, I don't know when we're gonna learn and live like this and just treat people like this, that we need to get rid of bitterness, rage, what an appropriate verse for this week.

28:51.549 --> 28:54.893
Anger, brawling, slander with every form of malice.

28:56.195 --> 28:59.759
Be kind and compassionate to one another, forgiving each other.

29:00.080 --> 29:00.440
How?

29:00.861 --> 29:02.002
Because he did it for you.

29:03.618 --> 29:05.200
In fact, let me go so far to say it this way.

29:05.480 --> 29:08.304
You'll never have to forgive somebody more than what Jesus forgave you.

29:10.807 --> 29:11.668
What about that thought?

29:12.689 --> 29:14.151
And here I'm holding and hating.

29:16.915 --> 29:17.675
It just can't be.

29:18.977 --> 29:23.383
Therefore, as here's another one, as God's chosen people, that's who you are, Highlands.

29:25.505 --> 29:29.851
I'm giving you your marching orders for this coming week and for the rest of your life.

29:30.491 --> 29:32.594
You're holy and dearly loved by God.

29:33.154 --> 29:34.997
Hey, you know what clothes yourself means?

29:35.297 --> 29:35.898
Put it on.

29:36.739 --> 29:37.661
It ain't on you right now.

29:38.121 --> 29:38.802
You get a choice.

29:38.843 --> 29:40.665
This is not a feeling, this is a choice.

29:41.426 --> 29:49.799
Clothes yourselves with compassion, kindness, humility, gentleness, patience.

29:49.819 --> 29:50.660
Bear with each other.

29:51.902 --> 29:53.184
I don't want to, too bad.

29:54.286 --> 29:56.289
Put it on, clothe yourself with it.

29:56.309 --> 29:58.372
I've just decided I'm not gonna get mad.

29:59.734 --> 30:00.555
That's what I've decided.

30:01.617 --> 30:02.418
Bear with each other.

30:02.658 --> 30:10.086
and forgive one another of any grievance that you have against someone.

30:10.106 --> 30:11.107
Chris, you're asking too much.

30:11.187 --> 30:14.210
No, I'm not because it's already happened to you.

30:16.612 --> 30:17.994
Jesus already did this for you.

30:18.054 --> 30:18.314
C.S.

30:18.354 --> 30:19.235
Lewis said it beautifully.

30:20.076 --> 30:26.903
To be a Christian means to forgive the inexcusable because God has forgiven the inexcusable in me.

30:28.805 --> 30:29.746
This is what we do.

30:31.906 --> 30:32.687
This is so good.

30:34.390 --> 30:38.417
And by the way, I don't have time to tell a little story, but I thought about another forgiveness story.

30:39.338 --> 30:45.528
And this one's the woman, the prostitute who had the alabaster jar, a perfume, pouring over Jesus' feet.

30:45.668 --> 30:49.635
And the Pharisees are mocking this whole situation, like does he even know?

30:50.056 --> 30:52.139
Does he even know who's doing that to him right now?

30:52.760 --> 30:54.903
He was the judgmental Pharisee.

30:56.566 --> 30:58.930
And Jesus said this, he goes, think about this.

31:00.098 --> 31:03.724
Two debts, one was just a few dollars, one was billions of dollars.

31:04.525 --> 31:05.547
Both are canceled.

31:06.188 --> 31:08.451
Which one of those two do you think is the most grateful?

31:10.334 --> 31:13.319
And the answer, of course, was the one who owed the most.

31:15.482 --> 31:17.445
And Jesus said, that's all of us.

31:17.465 --> 31:22.393
And then he goes on to say this, he who has been forgiven little loves little.

31:23.174 --> 31:28.082
So if you find yourself loving little, it's because you've only been forgiven little.

31:28.994 --> 31:32.800
But he who has been forgiven much loves much.

31:35.304 --> 31:39.630
And I'm calling on all of us to embody that, to release that to the world around us.

31:40.672 --> 31:43.416
I wrote a book this summer that's gonna come out in April.

31:44.377 --> 31:46.961
And it's my old age book.

31:47.061 --> 31:48.704
I'm not old, but I'm 62.

31:49.044 --> 31:52.690
And I said, I'm gonna write my life principles book, the ones that I've learned.

31:53.282 --> 32:00.230
where every chapter is, you can read it just, you can pick any chapter, you don't have to read it through, it's 30 principles, they're my life principles.

32:01.231 --> 32:18.211
And on a whim, as I was writing these, I summarized one of the chapters, I was like in chapter 20 something, and I had a hunch that I could write the principle all over again at the end of the chapter in letter form to my grandkids.

32:18.231 --> 32:20.914
So I wrote the principle and then I just said, dear grandkids,

32:21.506 --> 32:25.772
And then I said it in an endearing way, almost like a deathbed way, but I'm not dying.

32:26.353 --> 32:28.816
But I was in that frame of mind.

32:29.017 --> 32:32.321
Like, when I'm going, I want you to remember this.

32:32.341 --> 32:34.665
And so I ran down and I said, Tim, Tim, Tim, read this.

32:34.725 --> 32:35.466
What do you think about this?

32:36.608 --> 32:37.629
And so I came back three minutes later.

32:37.649 --> 32:39.812
She saw being on the couch and went, yes.

32:39.872 --> 32:40.313
It worked.

32:41.254 --> 32:46.281
And so I went back and I summarized every chapter in letter form, and I'm calling the book Legacy Letters.

32:47.203 --> 32:49.586
Timeless principles I've learned, lived, and lived behind.

32:50.562 --> 32:54.666
And chapter 20 something is the second chance principle, I call it.

32:55.006 --> 32:55.747
And here's how it goes.

32:56.428 --> 32:57.729
Get people a second chance.

32:57.749 --> 33:01.913
You never know when you're gonna need one too.

33:01.933 --> 33:08.620
And I'm just asking the world, can we just be a bit more gracious?

33:09.380 --> 33:10.582
Can we just be a bit more loving?

33:10.822 --> 33:14.265
Can we just imagine treating people the way Jesus treats us?

33:14.726 --> 33:15.326
I got it closed.

33:15.386 --> 33:16.327
Here's the last one.

33:16.347 --> 33:18.529
You don't get anything out of this today?

33:18.549 --> 33:19.250
Okay, number three.

33:20.450 --> 33:28.840
And that is once you receive it and then release it, then go represent it to the world publicly.

33:30.222 --> 33:30.902
Let me say it this way.

33:31.123 --> 33:34.406
The hope of this series is for not you to go home and go, who in God good?

33:35.508 --> 33:40.293
The hope of this series is for you to experience the goodness God so you can show that goodness to the world around us.

33:41.375 --> 33:47.602
And I closed with a heartbreaking story because it's where my mind went this week.

33:47.810 --> 34:03.227
I was reminded on June 17th, 2015, when a 21-year-old gunman went into Immanuel AME Church in Charleston, South Carolina, murdered nine people in the middle of a Wednesday night bulb study.

34:05.849 --> 34:06.590
I remember vividly.

34:08.472 --> 34:09.573
And they caught him the next day.

34:09.593 --> 34:15.280
And then two days later, within 48 hours, there was a hearing.

34:15.340 --> 34:17.522
There was like a bond hearing.

34:18.146 --> 34:27.079
where he was on video and the people who died, their families were there to confront this killer.

34:29.443 --> 34:32.487
And then they shocked the world.

34:32.507 --> 34:37.154
Because the daughter of victim, Ethel Lance, looked directly into the camera and said, I forgive you.

34:37.875 --> 34:47.730
Two days later, not a year later, two days later, the mother of Taiwan's as Sanders said, every fiber in my body hurts and I'll never be the same, but may God.

34:48.162 --> 34:49.023
grant you mercy.

34:50.285 --> 34:55.432
Reverend Anthony Thompson, the husband of Myra Thompson, told the gunman, I forgive you.

34:55.472 --> 34:57.475
Give your life to Jesus Christ.

34:57.535 --> 34:58.596
That's what really matters.

34:59.417 --> 35:00.098
Can you imagine?

35:01.300 --> 35:07.949
One pastor later reflected, their forgiveness was an extension of who they already are.

35:09.431 --> 35:11.594
It was like it was just part of them.

35:12.836 --> 35:14.418
And I thought, that's my hope.

35:14.914 --> 35:22.482
My hope is that we don't just believe this, learn this, know this, but we become this.

